originalText.text: This service helped me find my current therapist, who has been a great fit for my needs. Before finding this platform, I found it tremendously difficult to navigate finding a therapist that was a good fit for me and my unique life experiences, and MyWellbeing helped me filter by all my specific needs and only connected me to therapists who met them. I was able to set up an introduction call through the platform, so up until that point there was no phone calls needed. If you are someone that has "find a therapist" on your to do list, I would highly recommend this service as a great first step.

originalText.text: As a therapist working with MyWellbeing for over 5 years, they have done an excellent job of matching me with appropriate clients for my practice, making it easier for clients to find a good therapeutic fit and for me to find the clients that I am best suited to work with.

originalText.text: Very happy with my experience with MyWellbeing. Trying to find a therapist through my insurance was SO overwhelming. MyWellbeing asked me questions that were important to me when looking for a therapist, and gave me a couple of options to explore (not a phone book). The 15 minute introduction call is where the magic really happens- no $$, low pressure, and you can really get the feeling for how a regular conversation with the therapist would go without feeling obligated.

originalText.text: I want to warn other practitioners that this is an utter waste of money.  Not only do they wrongly identify a clinicians specialty when a potential client enters the particular type of therapy they seek, but there are few, if any, referrals of any kind.  Canceling your membership is an hour long, or more, process.  They clearly do not have the referral base that they initially claimed to have.

originalText.text: If you are a therapist, do not pay for this service. They have too many paying therapists and not enough clients for you to make a return (if you even land a client, at most you'll be flooded with emails from people that will never respond). They also claim to have 90k followers on instagram which is dishonest to say at the best as one can easily tell by the lack of engagement that they are lying and have therefore bought followers.
